; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk, grammars/form-eval.fk
;
; form-eval-band — form-eval (the Form meta-evaluator, in Form) now evaluates a fuller grammar:
; all binary builtins, let, defn, do, recursion, and user-defined-function CALLS — the meta-circular core.
; Each claim is fe-eval run on a SOURCE STRING; the value it computes pins the grammar form-eval interprets.
; The recipe under test is itself Form source, walked by a Form walker on the c-bootstrapped fkwu kernel —
; running a recipe no longer REQUIRES flattening; the cursor reads and computes directly.
;
; THE milestone (claim 64): (do (defn f (n) (add n 1)) (f 5)) -> 6 — a recipe with a USER-DEFINED function,
; run THROUGH form-eval. Claim 128: a recursive user function — sum 1..5 -> 15. Claim 256: factorial 5 -> 120.
;
; Verdict 1023 when every claim lands (each a distinct power of two). Every claim uses only the
; integer/list/string surface all four kernels carry — four-way honest.
;   1    integer literal:                  42 -> 42
;   2    first-stone binary op (add):      (add 40 2) -> 42
;   4    first-stone conditional (if/le):  (if (le 5 2) 111 999) -> 999
;   8    all binary ops (mul):             (mul 6 7) -> 42
;   16   comparison returns 1/0 (eq):      (eq 5 5) -> 1
;   32   lexical binding (let):            (let x 40 (add x 2)) -> 42
;   64   user-defined function CALL:       (do (defn f (n) (add n 1)) (f 5)) -> 6     <-- THE milestone
;   128  recursive user call:             (do (defn s (n) (if (le n 0) 0 (add n (s (sub n 1))))) (s 5)) -> 15
;   256  factorial (mul + recursion):      (do (defn fac (n) (if (le n 1) 1 (mul n (fac (sub n 1))))) (fac 5)) -> 120
;   512  two co-defined fns + nesting:     (do (defn dbl (x) (mul x 2)) (defn inc (x) (add x 1)) (dbl (inc 20))) -> 42
(do
    (defn k1 () (if (eq (fe-eval "42") 42) 1 0))
    (defn k2 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(add 40 2)") 42) 2 0))
    (defn k3 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(if (le 5 2) 111 999)") 999) 4 0))
    (defn k4 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(mul 6 7)") 42) 8 0))
    (defn k5 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(eq 5 5)") 1) 16 0))
    (defn k6 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(let x 40 (add x 2))") 42) 32 0))
    (defn k7 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(do (defn f (n) (add n 1)) (f 5))") 6) 64 0))
    (defn k8 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(do (defn s (n) (if (le n 0) 0 (add n (s (sub n 1))))) (s 5))") 15) 128 0))
    (defn k9 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(do (defn fac (n) (if (le n 1) 1 (mul n (fac (sub n 1))))) (fac 5))") 120) 256 0))
    (defn k10 () (if (eq (fe-eval "(do (defn dbl (x) (mul x 2)) (defn inc (x) (add x 1)) (dbl (inc 20)))") 42) 512 0))
    (add (k1) (add (k2) (add (k3) (add (k4) (add (k5) (add (k6) (add (k7) (add (k8) (add (k9) (k10)))))))))))
